data.Clinical History: Mr. Gandhi C R and Mrs. Manasa N are a second-degree consanguineous couple. Their first-born child was suspected of Maple Syrup Urine disease. They have an ongoing pregnancy of 23 weeks and 4 days GA. Anomaly scan at 23 weeks and 2 days GA revealed a single umbilical artery. Mrs. Manasa N and Mr. Gandhi C R have been evaluated for carrier status of pathogenic variations.
data.Depth: No pathogenic or likely pathogenic variant causative of the reported phenotype was detected
